o di volgarizzamenti in prosa di Passioni armonizzate, per lo più collocabili nell'Italia settentrionale, che erano finora sconosciuti o poco noti, evidenziandone i nessi e inserendoli nella tradizione del Diatessaron. Il lavoro è indirizzato dunque a cultori di linguistica e filologia italiana e romanza così come a chi si occupa di letteratura religiosa medievale e studi biblici.  aThis book provides an edition and a linguistic analysis of a Passion of the Christ written in old Milanese prose and preserved in a 15th-century manuscript. The study discusses the dating of this text, the geographical context, and its dependence on a Latin model. It also analyzes its relationship with other known prose Passions and identifies their sources. A concluding word glossary highlights the most interesting and obscure words and terms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 4aAltmailänder Dialekt. 4aAncient Lombard Dialects. 4aAncient Milanese. 4aGospel Harmony. 4aGospelharmonie. 4aItalienische Literaturgeschichte. 4aVernacular Translations of the Bible. 4aVolkssprachliche Bibelübersetzungen. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Historical & Comparative.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2016z9783110485257oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831104782800 cprintz978311047649140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311048028340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110480283423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110480283.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-de